					<div id="mw-content-text" class="mw-body-content"><div class="mw-content-ltr mw-parser-output" lang="en" dir="ltr"><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r15431463">.mw-parser-output .wst-author-mainblock{border:1px solid #BEA2A2;background-color:#E4D8D8}.mw-parser-output .wst-author-notes{border-bottom:1px solid #A88;background-color:var(--background-color-neutral,#FFFBFC);color:inherit}.mw-parser-output .wst-author-seealso{border:1px solid #CCC}@media screen{html.skin-theme-clientpref-night .mw-parser-output .wst-author-mainblock{background-color:#4B3434}}@media screen and (prefers-color-scheme:dark){html.skin-theme-clientpref-os .mw-parser-output .wst-author-mainblock{background-color:#4B3434}}</style><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r15675465">.mw-parser-output .wst-header-mainblock{margin:4px auto 4px auto;padding:0 3px;display:flex;align-items:center}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-back,.mw-parser-output .wst-header-forward{display:flex;flex:1 4 100%;min-width:min-content;align-items:center;font-size:.9em}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-nav-empty{visibility:hidden}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-back{justify-content:flex-start;text-align:left}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-central-cell{flex:4 1 100%;max-width:max-content;text-align:center}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-forward{justify-content:flex-end;text-align:right}@media(max-width:768px){.mw-parser-output .wst-header-mainblock{flex-wrap:wrap}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-central-cell{flex:0 0 100%;order:-2;width:auto}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-back,.mw-parser-output .wst-header-forward{width:auto}}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-notes{display:inline-block;border-collapse:collapse;border-spacing:0;empty-cells:hide;font-size:.9em;line-height:1.4;margin:0 auto 4px auto;width:100%}.mw-parser-output .wst-header-left{float:left}</style><div class="ws-header wst-header-structure wst-author wst-author ws-header"><div class="wst-header-mainblock wst-author-mainblock authortemplate"><div class="wst-header-back searchaux wst-author-back"><div class="wst-header-back-arrow">←</div><div class="wst-header-back-link"><a href="/wiki/Wikisource:Authors-Do" class="mw-redirect" title="Wikisource:Authors-Do">Author Index: Do</a></div></div><div class="wst-header-central-cell wst-author-central-cell"><span class="wst-header-title wst-author-title"><span style="font-weight:bold">Frederick Douglass</span><br />(1818–1895)</span></div><div class="wst-header-forward searchaux wst-author-forward wst-header-nav-empty"><div class="wst-header-forward-link"></div><div class="wst-header-forward-arrow">→</div></div></div><div class="wst-header-notes header&#95;notes searchaux wst-author-notes author&#95;notes"><style data-mw-deduplicate="TemplateStyles:r14791120">.mw-parser-output .plainSister{display:block;font-size:93%;line-height:normal;list-style-type:none;list-style-image:none;list-style-position:outside;border:1px solid var(--border-color-interactive--hover,#AAA);float:right;clear:right;margin:0.5ex 0 0.5ex 0.5ex;padding:0;background:var(--background-color-base,#FFFFFF);color:var(--color-base,#202122)}.mw-parser-output .sisicon,.mw-parser-output .dabicon{padding-right:1ex}</style><ul class="plainSister"><li class="sisitem"><span class="sisicon"><span typeof="mw:File/Frameless"><a href="/wiki/Special:SiteMatrix" title="Special:SiteMatrix"><img alt="Sister Projects" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Wikimedia-logo.svg/20px-Wikimedia-logo.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail" decoding="async" width="18" height="18" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/81/Wikimedia-logo.svg/40px-Wikimedia-logo.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail 2x" data-file-width="1024" data-file-height="1024" /></a></span></span><a href="/wiki/Special:SiteMatrix" title="Special:SiteMatrix">sister projects</a>: <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frederick_Douglass" class="extiw" title="w:Frederick Douglass">Wikipedia article</a>, <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Frederick_Douglass" class="extiw" title="c:Frederick Douglass">Commons gallery</a>, <a href="https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/Category:Frederick_Douglass" class="extiw" title="c:Category:Frederick Douglass">Commons category</a>, <a href="https://en.wikiquote.org/wiki/Frederick_Douglass" class="extiw" title="q:Frederick Douglass">quotes</a>, <a href="https://www.wikidata.org/wiki/Q215562" class="extiw" title="d:Q215562">Wikidata item</a></li></ul><div class="wst-header-content header&#95;notes&#95;content wst-header-notes-content wst-author-notes-content">
<p>American abolitionist, editor, orator, author, statesman and reformer; called "The Sage of Anacostia" and "The Lion of Anacostia,"; among the most prominent African Americans of his time and one of the most influential lecturers and authors in American history  <br /><i><span class="skin-invert-image" typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></span></span> one or more chapters are available in a spoken word format.</i>
</p>
</div></div><figure class="mw-default-size" typeof="mw:File/Thumb"><a href="/wiki/File:Frederick_Douglass_as_a_younger_man.jpg" class="mw-file-description"><img alt="" src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Frederick_Douglass_as_a_younger_man.jpg/250px-Frederick_Douglass_as_a_younger_man.jpg?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail" decoding="async" width="250" height="286" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/8b/Frederick_Douglass_as_a_younger_man.jpg/500px-Frederick_Douglass_as_a_younger_man.jpg?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail 2x" data-file-width="1739" data-file-height="1992" /></a><figcaption><div style="text-align:center">Frederick Douglass</div></figcaption></figure><div id="ws-data" class="vcard ws-noexport" style="display:none;speak:none"><span id="ws-article-id">12402</span><span id="wd-article-id">Q215562</span><span id="ws-name" class="fn">Frederick Douglass</span><span class="n"><span class="given-name">Frederick</span><span class="family-name">Douglass</span></span><span id="ws-commons">Frederick Douglass</span><span id="ws-description" class="note">American abolitionist, editor, orator, author, statesman and reformer; called "The Sage of Anacostia" and "The Lion of Anacostia,"; among the most prominent African Americans of his time and one of the most influential lecturers and authors in American history  <br /><i><span class="skin-invert-image" typeof="mw:File"><span><img src="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/20px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail" decoding="async" width="20" height="20" class="mw-file-element" srcset="//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Speaker_Icon.svg/40px-Speaker_Icon.svg.png?utm_source=en.wikisource.org&amp;utm_campaign=parser&amp;utm_content=thumbnail 2x" data-file-width="500" data-file-height="500" /></span></span> one or more chapters are available in a spoken word format.</i></span></div></div>
